Recursive Auxiliary Test.

This tests recursive auxiliary recipe calls. Computes the sum from 5 down to
1 (should output 15). The Summer sous-chef receives N on top of the first
mixing bowl, uses a loop as an if together with Set aside, recurses with
N minus 1, and leaves sum(N) as the only value in its first mixing bowl.

Ingredients.
5 g input
0 g sum

Method.
Put input into mixing bowl.
Serve with Summer.
Fold sum into mixing bowl.
Clean mixing bowl.
Put sum into mixing bowl.
Pour contents of the mixing bowl into the baking dish.

Serves 1.

Summer.

Ingredients.
0 g n
0 g m
0 g zero
1 g unit

Method.
Fold n into mixing bowl.
Clean mixing bowl.
Put zero into mixing bowl.
Check the n.
Put n into 2nd mixing bowl.
Remove unit from 2nd mixing bowl.
Fold m into 2nd mixing bowl.
Clean mixing bowl.
Put m into mixing bowl.
Serve with Summer.
Add n.
Fold m into mixing bowl.
Clean mixing bowl.
Put m into mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Check the n until checked.
Refrigerate.
